{
  "texts": [
    "Primarily, they exploited statistical features to analyze the text [24].",
    "Then, with the introduction of deep learning methods, it became possible to concentrate on more advanced syntactic and semantic features and to analyze the style and content of a text [4], applying LSTMs or Transformer-based models like BERT [12].",
    "For example, BERT has been employed to extract features to train a regression model [13], directly output a class label [49,54], or RoBERTa and Bi-LSTM have been combined to assess essays [5].",
    "Further, hand-crafted features in combination with existing LSTM or BERT structures have been shown to boost the performance [51].",
    "But overall, the models up to 2022 concentrate more on language than on content and do not emphasize cohesion and coherence of the essays enough [44]."
  ]
}